  <h2>Try it: drifted vs aligned design system</h2>
  <div class="tone-junior"><p>"Drifted" shows two micro-frontends side-by-side with different design system versions — notice the button border radius, spacing, and color token differences. "Aligned" shows the same two micro-frontends sharing a singleton — visually consistent across the boundary.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-mid"><p>Inspect the buttons in each mode. In drifted mode, the catalog button uses the v3 token scale (border-radius: 8px, gap: 12px) and the checkout button uses the v2 token scale (border-radius: 4px, gap: 8px). Same brand, two versions, silent divergence.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-staff"><p>Open DevTools → Sources in the drifted mode. You'll find both design system versions in the bundle — the same library shipped twice. In aligned mode, one version, shared. This is the bundle size argument alongside the visual consistency argument.</p></div>

